The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, January 21, 2004 				 Lid off loan racket
 Krishnagar (Nadia), Jan. 20:  Police today arrested three persons for allegedly running  a bank-loan racket and duping people in North 24-Parganas,  Howrah and parts of Nadia.																								The arrests came after Shantoshpur resident Prabir Majumdar lodged an FIR with Haringhata police station on Saturday. Majumdar, a Life Insurance Corporation employee, said Arun Mukherjee, Sujit Mukherjee and Pabitra Paul had cheated him of Rs 20, 000 after promising to arrange a Rs 300,000 loan from ICICI bank.																								Arun was arrested from Agarpara in North 24-Parganas last night and Sujit and Pabitra from Bali near Dhashineswar in Howrah.																								Those arrested are found to have cheated not only Majumdar but several others. We have booked them under cheating and forgery cases, Kalyani sub-divisional police officer Prasun Banerjee said, adding that the accused had confessed to the crime. 
